===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ojp|ja|sort=なし}}.  Derivation unclear, with numerous theories.  Two of the more common are given below.

: May be originally a compound of {{compound|lang=ja|sort=なし|中|tr1=na</i>, hypothesized root of modern <i>naka|t1=middle, center|白い|tr2=shiro|t2=white}} in reference to the pale flesh of the fruit.

: {{IPAchar|/na ɕiro/}} > {{IPAchar|/naɕi/}}

: Alternately, may be originally a compound of {{compound|lang=ja|sort=なし|中|tr1=na</i>, hypothesized root of modern <i>naka|t1=middle, center|酢|tr2=su|t2=sour, acidic}} in reference to the way the flavor of the fruit becomes more astringent closer to the core.

: {{IPAchar|/na su/}} > {{IPAchar|/naɕi/}}

